'''策略燒除'''（{{lang|en|Prescribed burn}}）<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hk01.com/%E5%91%A8%E5%A0%B1/390088/%E7%A7%91%E6%8A%80-%E6%9C%AA%E4%BE%86-%E5%85%A8%E7%90%83%E5%B1%B1%E7%81%AB%E7%87%92%E4%B8%8D%E7%9B%A1-%E5%A6%82%E4%BD%95%E9%9D%A0%E7%A7%91%E6%8A%80%E6%92%B2%E6%BB%85|title=【科技．未來】全球山火燒不盡　如何靠科技撲滅？|author=孔祥威|date=2019-10-25|website=香港01|access-date=2020-07-24|archive-date=2020-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200808155226/https://www.hk01.com/%E5%91%A8%E5%A0%B1/390088/%E7%A7%91%E6%8A%80-%E6%9C%AA%E4%BE%86-%E5%85%A8%E7%90%83%E5%B1%B1%E7%81%AB%E7%87%92%E4%B8%8D%E7%9B%A1-%E5%A6%82%E4%BD%95%E9%9D%A0%E7%A7%91%E6%8A%80%E6%92%B2%E6%BB%85|dead-url=no}}</ref>，又名'''控管燒除'''（{{lang|en|Controlled burn}}）或'''減危燒除'''（{{lang|en|hazard reduction burning}}）<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hillside.rfsa.org.au/fwhaz.htm|title=What is Hazard Reduction|author=|date=|website=www.hillside.rfsa.org.au|access-date=2020-07-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009145122/http://www.hillside.rfsa.org.au/fwhaz.htm|archive-date=2019-10-09|dead-url=yes}}</ref>是一種[[森林經營學|森林經營學]]行為，在受控的情況下人為引發小型山火，以減少日後發生大型且不受控之山火的機會<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pods.dasnr.okstate.edu/docushare/dsweb/Get/Document-9405/NREM-2894web.pdf|title=Managing Brush Fires|last=Weir|first=John|date=|website=|access-date=2020-07-25|archive-date=2016-09-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160910191543/http://pods.dasnr.okstate.edu/docushare/dsweb/Get/Document-9405/NREM-2894web.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。這種預防性的山火亦能促進森林生態循環及平衡。

策略燒除一般於非山火季進行以減少燃料的累積和減低發生嚴重山火的可能<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hillside.rfsa.org.au/lowintensityhrburn.pdf|title=Guidelines for Low Intensity Bushfire Hazard Reduction Burning|date=|website=|access-date=2009-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190312012412/http://www.hillside.rfsa.org.au/lowintensityhrburn.pdf|archive-date=2019-03-12|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。策略燒除能促進某些樹種的[[发芽|发芽]]並顯露泥土礦物層，以助更新森林。某些[[松毬|松毬]]與[[巨杉|巨杉]]更是只能在受熱的情況下才能傳播種子。

== 森林管理 ==
19世紀未的數次森林大火引致超過1500人喪生<ref name="Peshtigo">{{cite web|title=Firestorms of 1871 |work=Disasters |publisher=Boise State University |url=http://www.boisestate.edu/history/ncasner/hy210/peshtigo.htm |accessdate=July 27, 2007  |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070705191932/http://www.boisestate.edu/history/ncasner/hy210/peshtigo.htm |archivedate=July 5, 2007 }}</ref>，使當時政府認為山火會引起危害，因而建立必須被撲滅的理論體系<ref name="Aplet">{{cite journal| last =Aplet| first =Gregory H.| title =Evolution of Wilderness Fire Policy| journal =International Journal of Wilderness| volume =12| issue =1| pages =9–13| date =April 2006| url =http://www.wilderness.net/library/documents/IJWApr06_Aplet.pdf| accessdate =July 27, 2007| author =| archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20080228130826/http://www.wilderness.net/library/documents/IJWApr06_Aplet.pdf| archive-date =2008-02-28| dead-url =yes}}</ref>。20世紀初，一般皆認為山火在任何情況下皆應盡量撲滅<ref name="NRDC">{{cite web|title=Wildfires in Western Forests |publisher=Natural Resources Defense Council |date=May 2003 |url=http://www.nrdc.org/land/forests/pfires.asp |accessdate=July 27, 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070806021315/http://www.nrdc.org/land/forests/pfires.asp |archivedate=August 6, 2007 }}</ref>，而1935年[[美國國家森林局|美國國家森林局]]的指引更列明山火需在發現次日早上10時之撲滅<ref name="policy">{{cite web| title =Evolution of Federal Wildland Fire Management Policy| work =Review and Update of the 1995 Federal Wildland Fire Management Policy January 2001| publisher = National Park Service, U.S. Forest Service|date=January 2001| url =http://www.nifc.gov/fire_policy/docs/chp1.pdf| accessdate = July 27, 2007| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20061223095855/http://www.nifc.gov/fire_policy/docs/chp1.pdf| archivedate = December 23, 2006}}</ref>。

另一方面，20世紀一些研究人員則指山火有其對生態及環境的功用<ref name="tw">{{Cite web|url=https://np.cpami.gov.tw/%E5%85%AC%E5%9C%92%E5%B0%88%E6%AC%84/%E4%BB%96%E5%B1%B1%E4%B9%8B%E7%9F%B3/8704-%E6%B5%B4%E7%81%AB%E8%80%8C%E7%94%9F%E7%9A%84%E6%9D%89%E6%9C%A8%E7%BE%A4%EF%BC%8C%E4%B8%80%E8%A6%BD%E7%BE%8E%E5%9C%8B%E6%9D%89%E5%9C%8B%E5%AE%B6%E5%85%AC%E5%9C%92%E8%88%87%E7%95%B6%E5%9C%B0%E9%83%A8%E8%90%BD%E5%90%88%E4%BD%9C%E7%9A%84%E9%87%8E%E7%81%AB%E7%94%9F%E6%85%8B%E5%AD%B8.html|title=浴火而生的杉木群，一覽美國杉國家公園與當地部落合作的野火生態學|author=李文心|date=2019-03-20|website=臺灣國家公園公園專欄|access-date=2020-07-25|archive-date=2020-07-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200725120402/https://np.cpami.gov.tw/%E5%85%AC%E5%9C%92%E5%B0%88%E6%AC%84/%E4%BB%96%E5%B1%B1%E4%B9%8B%E7%9F%B3/8704-%E6%B5%B4%E7%81%AB%E8%80%8C%E7%94%9F%E7%9A%84%E6%9D%89%E6%9C%A8%E7%BE%A4%EF%BC%8C%E4%B8%80%E8%A6%BD%E7%BE%8E%E5%9C%8B%E6%9D%89%E5%9C%8B%E5%AE%B6%E5%85%AC%E5%9C%92%E8%88%87%E7%95%B6%E5%9C%B0%E9%83%A8%E8%90%BD%E5%90%88%E4%BD%9C%E7%9A%84%E9%87%8E%E7%81%AB%E7%94%9F%E6%85%8B%E5%AD%B8.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。例如生態學家[[奧爾多·利奧波德|奧爾多·利奧波德]]早於1924年就指出山火對生態系統的益處，並認為山火為植物的自然繁殖的必要過程之一。其後，更多生態學家加入支持這種理論，最終於1964年通過{{tsl|en|Wilderness Act|荒野保護法案}}，並促使森林管理局於1968年修改火災管理政策，確定如山火屬是自然引發，且不會對人命財產造成影響，則可允許其自然燃燒。管理局亦下令可按情況作策略燒除以回復生態系統平衡<ref name="policy"/>。

策略燒除通常使用{{tsl|en|driptorch|滴火槍}}以作引燃之用，滴火槍會流出一連串燃料並將其點燃。滴火槍亦能安裝於各種载具，甚至直升機之上。[[發焰筒|發焰筒]]和[[信號槍|信號槍]]亦能作遠距離點撚之用。

== 其餘策略燒除 ==

就中文語境中，策略燒除一般單指森林管理相關的人為山火，但英語中的「{{lang|en|Controlled burn}}」則可以泛指各種人為山火，例如[[刀耕火種|刀耕火種]]、燒除收割或伐木所產生的廢物也計算在內。亦有一種特殊的策略燒除為撲滅山火之時先行以火焰燒除燃料，以天然的防火道阻止山火前進，英語為「{{lang|en|Back burning}}」，而中文語境中一般亦不當作策略燒除之一。

